    "title": "SPRING PAPRIKA BASIL CHICKEN PASTA\u2728(FULL RECIPE BELOW) This creamy pasta is perfect for spring & Easter meals! I\u2019m using McCormick\u00ae Basil Leaves & Paprika to bring all the flavor without extra fuss, trusted in kitchens for 135 years! @McCormick Spices  It\u2019s easy, approachable, and the perfect weeknight pasta, you\u2019ll make it again and again! The KEY ingredients here are McCormick\u00ae Basil Leaves & Paprika to really bring out the flavor! Find more inspiration at McCormick.com \u2728 Chicken * 1 lb boneless skinless chicken breasts or thighs * 1 tsp salt * \u00bd tsp black pepper * 1 tsp garlic powder * 1 tsp basil * 1 tsp paprika * 1 tbsp olive oil Pasta & Sauce * 8 oz ditalini pasta * 2 tbsp butter * 2 garlic cloves, minced * \u00bd cup heavy cream * \u00bd cup grated Parmesan * 1 tsp basil * 1 tsp paprika * salt & pepper to taste * juice of 1 lemon * fresh basil, chopped Method 1. Season chicken: Toss chicken with salt, pepper, garlic powder, basil, and paprika. 2. Cook chicken: Heat olive oil in a skillet over medium-high heat. Cook chicken 4\u20135 minutes per side until golden and cooked through. Rest, then slice. 3. Make sauce: In the same pan melt butter. Add garlic and cook 30 seconds. Stir in cream, Parmesan, basil, paprika, salt, and pepper. Simmer 2\u20133 minutes until slightly thickened. 4. Cook pasta: Boil pasta until al dente. Drain and add to the sauce. 5. Finish: Add chicken, squeeze lemon juice over top, and toss. Garnish with fresh basil and serve! #McCormickPartner #Recipeshare #EasyRecipe #PastaLover #SpringMeals "
  },
